FFA Meeting
Signup and Info meetings
August 31st, 6:00 pm (JH and HS)
Sept. 2nd, 6:00 pm (Elementary)
AG Shop
FFA Dues are $25.00
We will be having two different times for the FFA Meeting. If you are unable to make the scheduled meeting of your student's classification please just let us know and make it to one of them. If you have a student that falls under both just pick one.
Booster Club will be at both meetings as well. They will be handing out information to parents that are interested in joining the Ropes Ag Boosters.
Mr. Edwards and I are looking forward to meeting you and preparing for another great year.
If you have any questions please feel free to call, text, or email us.

Shane Sherrill
Will Edwards

We will have a JH football parent and guardian meeting on Thursday, August 13th, 6:45 pm at the football field. Please sit on the home side. post_text:
P-EBT Applications are Now Open
The online application for the Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is now open for eligible families at yourtexasbenefits.com/Learn/PEBT (URL is case-sensitive). The Texas Education Agency (TEA) requests that districts and open-enrollment charter schools share the communication materials sent. The P-EBT application will be active through June 30, 2020. A P-EBT call center can be reached at 833-613-6220 to assist families in completing their application. Please review the "P-EBT Overview and Communications Toolkit" to the Administrator Addressed letter for additional information on the P-EBT program. All family outreach materials are available under Child Nutrition Guidance on the TEA Coronavirus (COVID-19) Support and Guidance website.

post_text:
2020 NHS Inductees
A virtual induction ceremony of new members of the Ropes High School National Honor Society was held on Friday, May 8th at 2 p.m. Existing members along with Mrs. Elkins, NHS adviser, Mr. Willmon, superintendent, Mrs. Ketchersid, secondary principal, Mr. Carter, assistant principal, Mrs. Luckie, counselor, and Mrs. Bratcher, yearbook adviser were in attendance, virtually. Trenity Wall, Bethany Richardson, Chloe Trull, and Megan Moore, all NHS officers, explained the characteristics of what members must exemplify. The following students were inducted for exhibiting the characteristics of scholarship, leadership, service, and character: Daley Moore, Ryan Terry (not pictured), Brenn Edwards, Aubrey O'Neal, Brogan Boyd, Harlee DePoyster, Andrew Moore (not pictured), and Drake Wyatt.
Congratulations to our new inductees.
